  "description": "Bilbao, the heart of the Basque Country, has transformed from an industrial port city into a vibrant cultural hub. The iconic Guggenheim Museum, with its titanium curves reflecting the Nervión River, symbolizes this metamorphosis. The city's medieval Old Town, Casco Viejo, contrasts with its modern architecture, while the lively pintxo bars serve up Basque culinary traditions. Bilbao's unique identity shines through its Euskera language signs, traditional cider houses, and the distinctive Basque beret worn by locals.",
